#. <html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta content="Pali text from the Mahāsaṅgīti Tipiṭaka Buddhavasse 2500" name="description"><title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="pli"><section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np26"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Pattavagga"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs0.5"
msgid ""
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs0.6"
msgid "26. Suttaviññattisikkhāpada"
msgstr "26. The training rule on asking for thread"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.256"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.26.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.142"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2350"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrel sanctuary."

#. From the origin story to <i lang="pli">pācittiya</i> 32 it seems <i lang="pli">cīvarakārasamaya</i> refers to any time one is making a robe, see <ref>MS.2.729</ref>.
#. VAR: bahuṃ suttaṃ → bahusuttaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū cīvarakārasamaye bahuṃ suttaṃ "
"viññāpesuṃ."
msgstr ""
"At that time the monks from the group of six were making robes, and they "
"asked for a large amount of thread."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Katepi cīvare bahuṃ suttaṃ avasiṭṭhaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"Yet even when their robes had been sewn, there was much thread left over."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.4"
msgid "Atha kho chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—"
msgstr "They said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.5"
msgid ""
"“handa mayaṃ, āvuso, aññampi suttaṃ viññāpetvā tantavāyehi cīvaraṃ "
"vāyāpemā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Well, let’s ask for more thread and get weavers to weave us robe-cloth.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū aññampi suttaṃ viññāpetvā tantavāyehi cīvaraṃ "
"vāyāpesuṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "Vītepi cīvare bahuṃ suttaṃ avasiṭṭhaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"Yet even when the robe-cloth had been woven, there was much thread left over."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.8"
msgid ""
"Dutiyampi kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū aññampi suttaṃ viññāpetvā tantavāyehi "
"cīvaraṃ vāyāpesuṃ."
msgstr ""
"For a second time they asked for more thread and got weavers to weave them "
"robe-cloth."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "Vītepi cīvare bahuṃ suttaṃ avasiṭṭhaṃ hoti."
msgstr "Once again there was much thread left over."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.10"
msgid ""
"Tatiyampi kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū aññampi suttaṃ viññāpetvā tantavāyehi "
"cīvaraṃ vāyāpesuṃ."
msgstr ""
"For a third time they asked for more thread and got weavers to weave them "
"robe-cloth."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.12"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā sāmaṃ suttaṃ viññāpetvā tantavāyehi "
"cīvaraṃ vāyāpessantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“How can the Sakyan ascetics ask for thread and then get weavers to weave "
"them robe-cloth?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2351"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.13"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.16"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sāmaṃ suttaṃ viññāpetvā tantavāyehi "
"cīvaraṃ vāyāpessantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six ask for thread and then get weavers "
"to weave them robe-cloth?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2352"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.17"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā "
"bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.18"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, sāmaṃ suttaṃ viññāpetvā tantavāyehi cīvaraṃ "
"vāyāpethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.143"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.21"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, sāmaṃ suttaṃ viññāpetvā tantavāyehi "
"cīvaraṃ vāyāpessatha."
msgstr ""
"Foolish men, how can you ask for thread and then get weavers to weave you "
"robe-cloth?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.22"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.23"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.23a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2353"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.24"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu sāmaṃ suttaṃ viññāpetvā tantavāyehi cīvaraṃ vāyāpeyya, "
"nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk himself asks for thread, and then gets weavers to weave him robe-"
"cloth, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs1.25"
msgid "(<em>26</em>:<strong>45</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.26.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2354"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2355"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "Sāmanti"
msgstr "Himself:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "sayaṃ viññāpetvā."
msgstr "he himself has asked."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2356"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.8"
msgid "Suttaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Thread:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.9"
msgid "cha suttāni—"
msgstr "there are six kinds of thread:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "khomaṃ kappāsikaṃ koseyyaṃ kambalaṃ sāṇaṃ bhaṅgaṃ."
msgstr "linen, cotton, silk, wool, sunn hemp, and hemp."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.257"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2357"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "Tantavāyehīti"
msgstr "Weavers:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: payoge payoge dukkaṭaṃ → payoge dukkaṭaṃ (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.12"
msgid "pesakārehi vāyāpeti, payoge payoge dukkaṭaṃ."
msgstr ""
"for every effort to get it woven by weavers, he commits an offense of wrong "
"conduct."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.144"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.13"
msgid "Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When he gets the robe-cloth, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.14"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr ""
"The robe-cloth should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.15"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.16"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""
"To be expanded as in <a class=\"cr\" href=\"./pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#13\">"
"Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17</a>, with appropriate substitutions. …"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.17"
msgid ""
"“idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ sāmaṃ suttaṃ viññāpetvā tantavāyehi vāyāpitaṃ "
"nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Venerables, this robe-cloth which I got woven by weavers after asking for "
"the thread myself is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.18"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.19"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.20"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.21"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe-cloth back to you.’”"

#. </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.21a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2358"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.22"
msgid "Vāyāpite vāyāpitasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he got it woven, and he perceives that he did, he commits an offense "
"entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.23"
msgid "Vāyāpite vematiko, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he got it woven, but he is unsure if he did, he commits an offense "
"entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.24"
msgid "Vāyāpite avāyāpitasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he got it woven, but he perceives that he did not, he commits an offense "
"entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2359"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.25"
msgid "Avāyāpite vāyāpitasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he did not get it woven, but he perceives that he did, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.26"
msgid "Avāyāpite vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he did not get it woven, but he is unsure if he did, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.27"
msgid "Avāyāpite avāyāpitasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If he did not get it woven, and he perceives that he did not, there is no "
"offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.27a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2360"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.28"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.29"
msgid "cīvaraṃ sibbetuṃ,"
msgstr "if it is to sew a robe;"

#. Āyoga. Used as a support for the pallattikā sitting posture. See TAP p.259 (ad. sek.26).
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.30"
msgid "āyoge,"
msgstr "if it is for a back-and-knee strap;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.31"
msgid "kāyabandhane,"
msgstr "if it is for a belt;"

#. VAR: aṃsabaddhake → aṃsavaṭṭake (bj) | aṃsabandhake (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.32"
msgid "aṃsabaddhake,"
msgstr "if it is for a shoulder strap;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.33"
msgid "pattatthavikāya,"
msgstr "if it is for a bowl-bag;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.34"
msgid "parissāvane,"
msgstr "if it is for a water filter;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.35"
msgid "ñātakānaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is from relatives;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.36"
msgid "pavāritānaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is from those who have given an invitation;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.37"
msgid "aññassatthāya,"
msgstr "if it for the benefit of someone else;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.38"
msgid "attano dhanena,"
msgstr "if it is by means of one’s own property;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.39"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.40"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2361"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np26:pts-cs2.41"
msgid "Suttaviññattisikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "The sixth rule, the training rule on asking for thread, is finished."

